      "index": 0,
      "text": "copy file \u0027../../Simple/.build/start.pr\u0027 to \u0027start-out.txt\u0027, overwrite",
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "indent": 0,
      "comment": "Drift case 1 \u2014 the load-bearing reason this branch exists.\n\nStep text \u0060- write out %message%\u0060 (from Tests/Simple/Start.goal:5) carries no\nchannel clause. With per-action notes (os/system/modules/output/write.notes.md)\ncarrying the channel routing rule only when output.write is in the planner\u0027s\nset, the LLM should emit:\nparameters: { Data: %message% }   (no channel key)\n\nPre-fix shape this test forbids:\nany \u0027channel\u0027 parameter on output.write when step text had no channel clause\n\nRead .pr requires copying to a .txt first because \u0027.pr\u0027 MIME deserializes to a\nGoal object, defeating substring assertions. Copy \u2192 read as text \u2192 assert.\nThe companion C# test PLang.Tests/Builder/CompilePromptTests/DriftCaseArtifactTests.cs\ndoes the structural check on the parsed Goal \u2014 both layers guard the same fact.\n\nArchitect\u0027s 3-fresh-cache verification rule runs externally:\nrm -rf Tests/Simple/.build\nPlangConsole/bin/Debug/net10.0/plang build /Tests/Simple   # then plang --test (x3)",
